'''Spring Mountain Vineyard''' is a 225 acre [[vineyard]] consisting of 135 different vineyard blocks scattered over the 845 acre estate in [[California]]'s [[Napa Valley]]. 

The original winery was established in [[1884]] and the current vineyards on the eastern slope of Spring Mountain at elevations varying from 400 to 1450 feet. Spring Mountain Vineyard achieved international recognition when it achieved fourth place at the [[Judgment of Paris (wine)|Judgment of Paris]].

